        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:27PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 425 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Addison, or 9 miles north of Hudson, moving east at 30 mph. There
are additional thunderstorms over northern Monroe County near Milan
that will also be capable of producing strong gusts.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Adrian, Monroe, Flat Rock, Tecumseh, Milan, Dundee, Carleton, Ida,
Petersburg, Onsted, Deerfield, Addison, Britton, Maybee, Cement City,
Clayton, La Salle, Gibraltar, Rockwood, and Rollin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
